<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="69" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[136,1452,157,364]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,318,157,183]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Comments</emphasis>
:—In Marambaia, it is found in Shrubby 
<emphasis box="[792,890,159,184]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Restinga</emphasis>
and Dense Submontane Ombrophilous Forest. It resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Don" authorityYear="1823" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1753" box="[253,337,194,220]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="hirta">
<emphasis box="[253,337,194,220]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">C. hirta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the bullate adaxial leaves surface, yet with moderate to dense cover of numerous setose, glandularsetose and stellate trichomes. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[470,685,230,256]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="urceolata">
<emphasis box="[470,685,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">Clidemia urceolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be sometimes mistaken with 
<taxonomicName authority="(Bonpland 1816: 5) Don (1823: 310)" authorityName="Don" authorityPageNumber="310" authorityYear="1823" baseAuthorityName="Bonpland" baseAuthorityPageNumber="5" baseAuthorityYear="1816" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="capitellata">
<emphasis box="[1073,1225,230,256]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">C. capitellata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Bonpland, A. J. A." box="[1240,1442,230,257]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="1799 - 1804" refId="ref23523" refString="Bonpland, A. J. A. (1816) Monographie des Melastomacees. Melastomes. In: Humboldt, F. H. A. &amp; Bonpland, A. J. A. (Eds.) Voyage aux regions equinoctials du Nouveau Continent, fait en 1799 - 1804, partie 6, Botanique, vol. 1. Lutetiae Parisiorum, Apud Gide Filium, Paris, 145 pp." type="book chapter" year="1816">Bonpland 1816: 5</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation author="Don, D." box="[136,322,266,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="276 - 329" refId="ref24307" refString="Don, D. (1823) An illustration of the natural family of plants called Melastomaceae. Memoirs of the Wernerian Natural History Society 4 (2): 276 - 329." type="journal article" year="1823">Don (1823: 310)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Don (1823: 307)" authorityName="Don" authorityPageNumber="307" authorityYear="1823" box="[361,686,265,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Clidemia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="neglecta">
<emphasis box="[361,488,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="69">C. neglecta</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Don, D." box="[495,686,265,292]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="276 - 329" refId="ref24307" refString="Don, D. (1823) An illustration of the natural family of plants called Melastomaceae. Memoirs of the Wernerian Natural History Society 4 (2): 276 - 329." type="journal article" year="1823">Don (1823: 307)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
], a related species that differs by its conspicuous bracteoles, and less dense glandular-pubescence (
<bibRefCitation author="Wurdack, J. J." box="[470,644,302,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="115 - 130" refId="ref28093" refString="Wurdack, J. J. (1971) Certamen Melastomataceis XVI. Phytologia 21: 115 - 130." type="journal article" year="1971">Wurdack 1971</bibRefCitation>
). Additional illustrations in 
<bibRefCitation author="Cogniaux, A." box="[968,1151,302,328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="1 - 510" refId="ref24081" refString="Cogniaux, A. (1883 - 1888) Melastomaceae. In: Martius, C. F. P., Eichler, A. G. &amp; Urban, I. (Eds.) Flora brasiliensis 14 (3): 1 - 510, (4): 1 - 656." type="journal article" year="1883">Cogniaux (1883</bibRefCitation>
–1888) and 
<bibRefCitation author="Matsumoto, K. &amp; Martins, A. B." pageId="8" pageNumber="69" pagination="19 - 22" refId="ref25752" refString="Matsumoto, K. A &amp; Martins, A. B. (2009) Clidemia. In: Wanderley, M. G. L., Shepherd, G. J., Melhem, T. S., Giulietti, A. M. &amp; Martins, S. E. (Eds.) Flora Fanerogamica do Estado de Sao Paulo, v. 6. Instituto de Botanica, FAPESP, Sao Paulo, pp. 19 - 22." type="book chapter" year="2009">Matsumoto &amp; Martins (2009)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
